description:
&lt;p&gt;We have a fantastic opportunity for a Principle Family Therapist to lead a highly respected and supportive family therapy team here at Milton Keynes Specialist CAMHS (MK Sp CAMHS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The family therapy team is part of a large, well-established and supportive multi-disciplinary team which also includes Psychiatrists, Psychologists, Nurses, Psychotherapists, Art Therapists and Primary Mental Health Practitioners; who have a healthy appreciation for the role of systemic thinking, in the context of complexity within family and professional systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The entire CAMHS service are housed together which allows for quick and easy access with other colleague and specialities. Strong collaborative working relationships are the norm along with the transfer of knowledge and skills between disciplines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Management has an open door policy for all staff members which promotes communication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MK Sp CAMHS are in the process of moving to the I-Thrive model, this will give you an exciting opportunity to influence service provision across Milton Keynes for young people and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is opportunity for flexible working that is in keeping with the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced, skilled and highly motivated Family Therapist for a full-time post on our team. We expect you to have an avid interest as well as experience in working with children, young people and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for the development, management and supervision of the family therapy provision across the Generic Sp CAMHS service and the specialist multi-disciplinary Eating Disorders team offering services to children &amp; young people meeting eligibility criteria for MK Sp CAMHS. You will provide systemic assessments and highly specialist systemic psychotherapy to the family systems referred to the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of the leadership structure within the team and participate in clinical risk management, audit, service evaluation and research in addition to the supervision of family therapists and other disciplines. It is therefore essential that you can demonstrate both the ability for autonomous thinking and multi-disciplinary team work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameTessa SaundersJob titleCAMHs Clinical LeadEmail addresstessa.saunders2@nhs.netTelephone number01908 724 544.&lt;/p&gt;
